Name.BusinessNameLine1: FSL Rural Development Inc and Subsidiary

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: PROVIDES LOW-INCOME ELDERLY PERSONS WITH HOUSING FACILITIES AND SERVICES SPECIALLY DESIGNED TO MEET THEIR PHYSICAL, SOCIAL, AND PSYCHOLOGICAL NEEDS.
IRS990.MissionDescription: FSL Rural Development offers affordable housing throughout Arizona providing individual apartments for low-income seniors and adults with disabilities.
IRS990.Description: The housing Program provides appropriate home choices for seniors and individuals with mobility and specific ability requirements. Residents are encouraged to personalize their surroundings and enjoy neighbors and communal activities. FSL Rural Development consists of four well maintained facilities located throughout the state. Residents served were 146 at the following facilities:Amy Neal Retirement Center - Kingman, AZVianney Villas - Avondale, AZPadua Hills - Wickenburg, AZSt. Agnes - Williams, AZIn 2002, FSL Rural Development Corporation became the managing and sole member of FSL South Mountain LLC. FSL South Mountain LLC guarantees, to the extent of its assets, the payment and performance of obligations of FSL Roeser Village, Inc., a related entity, as defined in the Guaranty Agreement. FSL South Mountain LLC is required to maintain a net worth of $400,000, of which $200,000 must be liquid pursuant to its guarantee requirements. These assets are reported in these financial statements as restricted cash.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: Funds collected as security deposits, under contractual agreements, are maintained in a separate fund. The amount maintained in the trust account is to be at least equal to the related tenant security deposit liability.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: FSL Rural Development Corporation and Subsidiary, a non-profit Arizona Corporation, has been granted certificates of exemption from payments of federal and state income taxes under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986. FSL South Mountain LLC, a wholly owned LLC, is a disregarded entity for income tax purposes as it is a sole member LLC. The Project has adopted the provisions of FASB Accounting Standards Codification Topic ASC 740-10 (previously Financial Interpretation No. 48, Accounting for Uncertainty in Income Taxes), on July 1, 2009. The implementation of this standard had no impact on the financial statements. As of both the date of adoption, and as of June 30, 2010, the unrecognized tax benefit accrual was zero. The Project will recognize future interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits in income tax expense if incurred. The Project is no longer subject to Federal tax examinations by tax authorities for years before 2006 and state examinations for years before 2005.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Everyone on Boards or working for the Foundation and its Affiliates are covered under the policy. For Foundation, conflicts are determined at the FSL Board level. For Affiliate corporations, conflicts are determined either at the FSL Leadership Council level or the affiliate board level for both the Level at which determinations of whether a conflict exists are made and the level at which actual conflicts are reviewed. All potential conflicts of interest, regardless of how small or insignificant, are to be reported to the President of the Board of Directors (or Committee Chair) prior to engaging in a conflict of interest board or committee action. The President will ask the Board of Directors to make a decision as to whether the relationship is an appropriate one for FSL. The Board member declaring the conflict will have no vote on the matter. Moreover, the person having a conflict shall retire from the room in which the Board (or its Committee) is meeting and shall not participate in the final deliberation regarding the matter under consideration. However, the person shall be permitted to provide the Board or Committee with any and all relevant information prior to leaving the meeting.

Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: The Top Management Official is Steve Hastings. Steve Hastings is compensated by a related organization and his compensation is approved by Guy Mikkelsen, President and CEO for services provided to this organization and other related organizations. Compensation studies are done to determine appropriate compensation for his level and role. Guy Mikkelsen is compensated by a related organization, Foundation for Senior Living, Inc. (FSL) for his services provided to FSL and its related organizations. His compensation is approved by the governing board of FSL. On an annual basis, they are provided with comparability data/compensation studies to determine his compensation. Other officers are provided compensation from FSL and other related organizations for their services, beyond the governing board, provided to that entity and other related organizations. Their compensation is approved by Guy Mikkelsen, President and CEO. The organization is expanding the review by independent persons for the upcoming fiscal year. During the year, FSL and its related organizations used an independent consultant to perform a market study analysis on compensation across several industries.
